This directory contains a modified fork of Trajectron++
(https://github.com/StanfordASL/Trajectron-plus-plus), originally
released under the MIT License by the Stanford Autonomous Systems Lab.

Modifications made for this work:
- Added CONE node type support for modeling traffic cones as scene agents
- Extended map encoder to accept additional heatmap channels (drivable-area)
- Added work-zone-specific data preprocessing pipeline
- Integrated cone raster / PointNet / scene-graph encoding modes (B-A/B-B/B-C)
- Modified evaluate.py to support cached heatmap input and work-zone metrics
- Added environment building scripts for SUMO simulation data

Original Trajectron++ paper:
  Tim Salzmann, Boris Ivanovic, Punarjay Chakravarty, Marco Pavone.
  "Trajectron++: Dynamically-Feasible Trajectory Forecasting With
  Heterogeneous Data." ECCV 2020.

